<note>A  This room is filled with the blinding Cloud of Chaos. Any
Hero who enters this room cannot see the other doors in the
room, so do not place them on the gameboard at this time.
(Monsters may not enter this room.) If a Hero enters the
room, he must stop and roll 1 red die:
<ul>
<li>If a Hero rolls a "1" or "2" on the die, he ends up back in
the corridor on the square marked 1/2.</li>
<li>If a Hero rolls a "3," "4," or "5," place one door in the
position shown next to the square with the corresponding
number rolled. Then, move the Hero through the door to the
corresponding number. If the square is occupied, the Hero
moves back into the room and treats his roll as a "6." See
directions that follow.</li>
<li>If a Hero rolls a "6," the Cloud of Chaos attacks and the
Hero must roll 1 combat die. If a skull is rolled, he and
any other Hero in the room lose 1 Body Point.</li>
</ul></note>
<note>B  This chest contains 250 gold coins. It also has a trap with an
exploding lock. If a Hero searches for treasure before the trap
has been disarmed, he will lose 3 Body Points.</note>
<note>C  This cliff corridor is Grin’s Crag. The first player who moves
